4 Theme Parks, 2 Water Parks and a World of Fun









With so much to see and do at Walt Disney World Resort this summer, you and your family can make magical vacation memories to last a lifetime. Enjoy 4 theme parks and 2 water parks, each with immersive attractions and experiences. Plus, explore Disney Springs, a breezy promenade brimming with restaurants, shops and entertainment.  







Disney’s Animal Kingdom Park
Delve into the magic of nature! Embark on a tour of a lush savanna that’s home to exotic animals on Kilimanjaro Safaris. Avoid the clutches of the mythic Yeti aboard a runaway train at Expedition Everest. And beginning May 27, 2017, discover the awe-inspiring land and immersive attractions of Pandora – The World of Avatar.










Disney’s Hollywood Studios
Thrill to Hollywood at its best! Race LA’s freeways on Rock ‘n’ Roller Coaster Starring Aerosmith. Test your aim at Toy Story Mania! Hurtle up and down The Twilight Zone Tower of Terror or feel the Force during Star Wars: A Galactic Spectacular. And starting May 26, 2017, celebrate tunes from Cars, Toy Story and more with The Music of Pixar Live!










Epcot
Travel the globe, into outer space and beyond! Fly over scenic wonder of the world on Soarin’. Sail on a musical ride through Arendelle on Frozen Ever After. Rev across rough terrain at Test Track or behold the story of our planet during IllumiNations: Reflections of Earth. Plus, through May 29, 2017, enjoy the Epcot International Flower & Garden Festival!










Magic Kingdom Park
Make dreams come true in a world of fantasy! Race through a diamond mine aboard Seven Dwarfs Mine Train. Brave a spine-tingling tour of the Haunted Mansion or be immersed in enchanted storytelling with the Once Upon a Time nighttime show. And conclude your day in a spectacular way with the new Happily Ever After fireworks show.










Disney’s Typhoon Lagoon Water Park
Splash land into a storm of excitement! Embark on a thrilling voyage along Miss Adventure Falls. Ride a gnarly wave at the Typhoon Lagoon Surf Pool. Catch air on a coaster-type ride atop slippery slides at Crush ‘n’ Gusher—or gather the group for a scenic rafting excursion past rocky caverns at Gangplank Falls. 










Disney’s Blizzard Beach Water Park
Find frosty fun at this watery wonderland! Feel your cares melt away as you glide on an inner tube at Cross Country Creek. Plunge 12 stories on a near-vertical drop at Summit Plummet or race against a friend at the Downhill Double Dipper. Plus, little ones can splash and play at Ketchakiddee Creek.










Disney Springs
Enjoy eclectic dining and shopping at over 75 unique venues! Explore brand-name boutiques like Uniqlo and Zara, and pick up keepsakes at World of Disney. Find live entertainment around every corner—and be dazzled by Cirque du Soleil. And savor the dining delights of STK, Morimoto Asia and Frontera Cocina. 








Vacation Planning Tips

Pick up some tips for your upcoming trip with our planning guides, including information on fun attractions and experiences for little ones, tweens, and grandparents!



 




